The paper proposes a novel approach to causal discovery from multiple datasets using causal modeling. This falls under the broad category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of background knowledge and interventions, which are relevant to the sub-categories of computational engineering (cs.CE) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper applies the proposed approach to flow cytometry protein expression data, which is a topic in the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SI).
